The error is due to incorrect assignment of a value from one record to anot
another. The 'selected' object should directly take the 'points', which com
comes from profile.score, without any other fields. Therefore, it should lo
look like this:

```Tundra
val raw = {
  profile: {
    name: "Ada",
    score: 12
   }
};

val profile = raw.profile;
val selected = profile.score; // Directly use the value from 'score' field 
of the profile record

print(selected);
```
This will print out `12` which is expected as per the program requirements.
requirements. The Tundra language uses dot notation to access fields, so we
we only need to write `profile.score` instead of trying to put it inside an
another object with 'points' key.
